problems as long as the availability is appropriate.  Melee items drop off various mobs, and while each and every spell might not be easy to get, in general we should see spells all over the place, with the better variety dropping off named mobs the way melee items do.  <br><br>In short, if we have 5 level 60 spells available, we complain because of the difficulty of getting the two top spells is very very difficult.  But if we had 30 level 60 DD spells available, with only the two two, or even 5 comming off specific mobs that are very difficult, the rest being good spells, then we wouldn't have as much of a reason to complain.<br><br>Sunstrike came out with 1615 damage, and dropped off a number of different level 60+ mobs.  Sure it isn't EASY to get, but it's available.  Velious gave us nothing new since Ice Spear of Solist has the lame 5 second recast delay and in general isn't an UPGRADE from Sunstrike.  So, to date, we had Ice Comet, Sunstrike, Elnerick's Electrical Rending, and Garrison's Supperior Sundering for the big blasts.  Seems that we should have seen a 1615 damage spell that would take 10 seconds to cast, and a version that could cast in 4 seconds.  Perhaps a version that casts in 3 seconds but has a recast delay, and a version that does 1800 damage, and a version that does 1400 damage.  Extend this model, spread them around, and bingo, a lot of problems are solved with class balance.<br> <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>Level 60 Wizard<br>The First Seal<br>The Nameless Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/02 12:18:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not an upgrade</span><hr size=1> 7.0  + 2.5 1615 damage @ 450 mana (3.59 ratio)<br>3.5 + 2.5 + 10.5 1200 damage @ 300 mana (4.0 ratio)<br><br>Is it just me, or isn't spear-sunstrike-spear-sunstrike a 3.75 ratio 170.6 DPS combo?<br><br>Vs 170.0 3.59 DPS from just sunstrike?<br><br>I mean, isn't that an upgrade comparable to primal velium weapons?  ;-)<br><br>It is 5% more efficient!<br><br>hehe.<br><br>The reason why there isn't that many spells is because of spell book room.  Until they get around to rewriting the PC character files (ahum), your spell book can't get bigger.<br><br>They could allow you to &quot;overscribe&quot; a varient of a spell, I guess.  Would you get the old spell you had scribed back?  If not, they'd have to publish more details of spells in-game, or people would get all upset when they downgraded a good spell.  Hell, the'll get upset even IF they publish more details of spells.<br><br>...<br><br>Oooo, they could allow you to unscribe spells to NO DROP, rescribeable versions of a spell.  It would solve the space&amp;clutter problems in spellbooks!<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udamoens.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damoen S</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/02 10:34:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not an upgrade</span><hr size=1> Sir Yakk  I disagree with your numbers.  Strictly on the fact that you do not take into account Meditation time in your DPS.  Therefore it is not a true account of DPS.  When you add in the Meditation time on all our spells the DPS falls through the floor.<br><br>As far as equipment vs spells.  The only mob dropped equipment that increases damage is FT items.  For some reason VI I guarding those items like a drowning man guards his air.  As for focus items I still think they are nothing more than trinkets, yet another bone thrown to wizards.  <br><br>I am still sitting on the fence about increasing the number of spells.  While on the surface it seems like a nice idea.  The numbers you quoted seem a little extreme and confusing.  Now I am not against gaining a couple spells per level that have different casting time, mana, damage, effects, resist types.  But I am uncertain about such a drastic increase in spells.<br><br>I remeber 3 years ago when an idea similar to this one started on these boards.  That one only called for increaseing the diversity of resist types per spell level.  You know getting  a fire, magic, and ice spell every level. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=721.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=721.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=721.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=721.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to re